<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Login Verification Code</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #333;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
    }
    .container {
      max-width: 600px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 20px;
    }
    .header {
      background-color: #232f3e;
      padding: 20px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .header h1 {
      color: #ffffff;
      margin: 0;
    }
    .content {
      padding: 20px;
      background-color: #f5f5f5;
    }
    .otp-container {
      background-color: #ffffff;
      border: 1px solid #ddd;
      border-radius: 5px;
      padding: 20px;
      margin: 20px 0;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .otp {
      font-size: 32px;
      font-weight: bold;
      letter-spacing: 5px;
      color: #232f3e;
    }
    .footer {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 20px;
      font-size: 12px;
      color: #777;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="header">
      <h1>Amazon Clone</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="content">
      <h2>Login Verification Code</h2>
      <p>Hello <%= name %>,</p>
      <p>You are receiving this email because you are trying to log in to your Amazon Clone account. To complete the login process, please use the verification code below:</p>
      
      <div class="otp-container">
        <div class="otp"><%= otp %></div>
      </div>
      
      <p>This code will expire in <%= expiresIn %>.</p>
      <p>If you did not request this code, please ignore this email and make sure you can still log in to your account. Someone may have typed your email address by mistake.</p>
      <p>Thank you for using Amazon Clone!</p>
    </div>
    <div class="footer">
      <p>This is an automated email, please do not reply.</p>
      <p>&copy; <%= new Date().getFullYear() %> Amazon Clone. All rights reserved.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>